column5: Dave could have just tossed this Motor/Tank on his curb and let the first Joe Blow driving by take it.  But instead he posted it on the OFC as FREE.  Man I love this Forum.  Not only do I learn something new every day, but I also have a chance to get free stuff  Thank you so much Dave  Check out the pic.  Sweat eh!! Definitly worth the 3 hour round trip to the city.
It's actually a 35Hp with a 25 cover..
You are most welcome Nick, good to meet you. Post a pic when you get out with it and get some fisheees.  Cheers,  Davo
I love OFC 2
"lucky" haha
Good stuff, glad you were able to get it, very nice of  Davo to offer it up...  Maureen
I see the OFC Anthem link has disappeared...may be time to post this again!
Sweet deal on the motor!  The Anthem and Cliff!  I haven't seen either of you in so long!

If anybody has a late model Yamaha F115 laying around.... I'm just sayin' Great score on the motor and kudos to Davo!

It needs a $200 pinion gear.  And I had one on an old evenrude that I sold for $150  two months ago!!  After it's running, it'l be worth atleast $900 eh?  Someone was trying to sell the exact same motor on Kijiji for $1250 last month, that seems a little high.
